|year=2008
|pmid=18587704}}</ref> They can cause infections such as [[scrapie]] in sheep, [[bovine spongiform encephalopathy]] ("mad cow" disease) in cattle, and [[chronic wasting disease]] in deer; in humans, [[Prion#Prion disease|prionic diseases]] include [[Kuru (disease)|Kuru]], [[Creutzfeldt–Jakob disease]], and [[Gerstmann–Sträussler–Scheinker syndrome]].<ref name="isbn0-12-375147-0">{{vcite book |author=Belay ED and Schonberger LB |title=Desk Encyclopedia of Human and Medical Virology |publisher=Academic Press |location=Boston |year=2009 |pages=497–504 |isbn=978-0-12-375147-8}}</ref>

